Question1) What is Python? What are the ways to install python in your PC?
Ans)Python is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose programming language. Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991, Python's design philosophy emphasizes code readability with its notable use of significant whitespace.

There are many ways to Install Python in our PC:

1) Installing Anaconda which comes with several other libraries.
-Search for www.anaconda.com on your web browser.
-Go to products---> Individual Edition
-Scroll down to Anaconda Installers
-Click on any of the python installers there depending on your system O.S. Do install python 3.7 version and 64 bit to 2 bit depending on your system requirement
-Once the download is completed, run the installer and click on subsequent next buttons and finally finish to complete the installation.

2)Installing Python which has separate libraries(For windows)
-Search for www.python.org on your web browser.
-Click python download.
-Click windows link.
-Click on the download windows x86-64 executable installer link under the top-left stable release.
-Move this file to a more permanent location, so that you can run the installer and complete the installation process

Question 2) What are code environments? What are its types?

Ans)A code environment is a standalone and self-contained environment to run Python or R code. Each code environment has its own set of packages. Environments are independent: we can install different packages or different versions of packages in different environments without interaction between them.

There are three main types of environments:
1. Text editors: General editors for any text file, works with a variety of file types, can be customised with plugins and add-ons.
Most popular- Visual studio, Atom

2.Full IDEs: Development environments designed specifically for python and has special functionalities, larger programs and only community editions are free.
Most Popular-PyCharm and Spyder

3. Notebook Environments: Great for learning, we can see input and output next to each other. It supports inline markdown notes, visualizations, videos and more. They do not have file format like .py.
Most popular- Jupyter Notebook
